### Finding M-003: Backup Restoration Test — RTO Near-Miss

**Source:** Quarterly backup restoration test, Week 11 post-authorization

**Finding:** Quarterly restoration test completed successfully — all data integrity verification checks passed. However, restoration completion time was 3 hours 47 minutes, compared to 2 hours 47 minutes in the prior test (Day 55). The RTO target is 4 hours. The test passed, but the margin has narrowed by one hour in one quarter.

**Response:**

Step 1 — Analyze cause: IT Administrator reviewed the restoration process timing. Identified two factors: (1) the OpenMRS database has grown by approximately 15% in one quarter as the system moves into full clinical operation; (2) the weekly S3 export job that creates the restoration source has been running successfully but the restoration procedure assumes a specific export format that changed slightly when the S3 export job was updated in Week 7.

Step 2 — Evaluate trend: At the current growth rate, the database will be approximately 60% larger at the next quarterly test than it was at authorization. If restoration time scales linearly with data volume, the RTO could be exceeded within two quarters.

Step 3 — Corrective action: IT Administrator updated the restoration procedure to reflect the current S3 export format. Estimated the restoration time improvement from the format fix: approximately 20-25 minutes. The data volume growth requires a more substantive response — either optimizing the restoration procedure (more parallelism in the RDS restoration, pre-staging the backup before the maintenance window begins) or revising the RTO target if clinical operations can tolerate a longer recovery window.

**Disposition:** Monitoring log entry: [date] — Quarterly restoration test passed. RTO: 3:47 — within target but trending toward limit. Procedure updated for S3 export format. RTO trend review scheduled for discussion with Health IT Manager and ISSO at 45-day CP-2 condition check-in with AO. POA&M entry created — M-003. Low severity. Owner: IT Administrator. Target: Restoration procedure optimization or RTO revision within 60 days.

**AO notification required?** Not immediately — the RTO target was met. The trend warrants mention in the quarterly POA&M report to the AO so the AO is aware before a future test misses the target.

