### Finding M-004: Quarterly Access Review — Role Assignment Discrepancy

**Source:** Quarterly access recertification, Week 12 post-authorization

**Finding:** The updated access review template (POA&M Item 010 remediation) prompted the Health IT Manager to evaluate role accuracy, not just account continuation. Using the new template, the Health IT Manager identified one user — a clinical staff member who transitioned from a full clinician role to a clinic administrative coordinator role — whose OpenMRS role remained set to Clinician with full encounter documentation access. The user had been in the administrative role for approximately six weeks before the access review identified the discrepancy.

**Response:**

Step 1 — Assess exposure: The ISSO reviewed the OpenMRS application audit log for the user's activity during the six-week period with incorrect role assignment. The audit log showed seven login sessions, all accessing administrative functions — no access to clinical encounter records during this period. The misconfigured role existed but was not exploited.

Step 2 — Immediate correction: IT Administrator updated the user's OpenMRS role from Clinician to Administrative Staff. Health IT Manager certified the updated assignment. Change documented in access review record.

Step 3 — Root cause review: The role assignment was not updated at the time of the job function change because there was no formal HR-to-ISSO notification process for internal role changes. Terminations trigger ISSO notification (PS-4 process). But internal transfers between departments did not — creating a gap in the access management lifecycle.

**Disposition:** Finding closed — role corrected, no exploitation. However, the root cause (no ISSO notification for internal role changes) requires a process update. The CM-3 change management procedure covers system-level changes; the HR/organizational change process needs to be updated to notify the ISSO of internal role changes that affect required system access levels.

POA&M entry created — M-004. Low severity. Owner: Health IT Manager + ISSO. Remediation: Update HR/onboarding and role-change process to include ISSO notification for any job function change that may affect system access requirements. Target: 45 days.

This finding is also a validation of the A-5 remediation value. The prior access review template would not have caught this — the Health IT Manager would have confirmed "this person still works here and needs OpenMRS access" without catching that the access level no longer matched the job function.

**SSP update required?** Yes — AC-2 implementation description should note that ISSO notification is required for internal role changes affecting system access, not just employee terminations.

